In the night, he was "drinking whiskey and writing".
The confidential history of Scotney is a relatively large unknown, as the National Trust organization gained access to documents only in 2006 after the death of the last heir, Elizabeth Hussey.
When Rhodes arrived ten years later, the staff began to penetrate into the archives that Rhodes described in words, as if "the Aristocrats of many centuries were throwing their hands around, saying, "Take it to the attic."
Journals, letters from the time of the British Empire, maps depicting property: “Maybe you think the dispute about land is boring,” Rhodes said, “but I found one case where two families were pulling the edge.
